---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';

const lastUpdated = '3 June 2026';
---

<StarlightPage
	frontmatter={{
		title: 'Privacy policy',
		description:
			"What personal data gaffer.kurrent.io collects, why, where it's stored, and your rights.",
		tableOfContents: false,
	}}
	hasSidebar={false}
>
	<p><em>Last updated {lastUpdated}</em></p>

	<p>
		We collect a small amount of personal data when you visit
		<code>gaffer.kurrent.io</code>: website analytics (only if you accept) and
		standard hosting logs. This covers the documentation website only. Telemetry
		that the gaffer CLI and VS Code extension send is a separate matter,
		documented at <a href="/telemetry/">/telemetry</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Who we are</h2>
	<p>
		<strong>Kurrent, Inc.</strong> operates this site and is the data controller
		for the purposes of GDPR and equivalent laws. Contact for anything in this
		policy, including subject-access and deletion requests:
		<a href="mailto:privacy@kurrent.io">privacy@kurrent.io</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>What we collect</h2>

	<h3>Analytics</h3>
	<p>
		If you click <strong>Accept</strong> on the cookie banner, we load PostHog,
		which records page URL, referrer, viewport, browser, OS, and a coarse
		country/region inferred from your IP (the raw IP is discarded at ingest).
		PostHog assigns an anonymous identifier so repeat visits can be told apart
		from new ones. We do not enable session replay, heatmaps, autocapture, or
		any third-party advertising integrations.
	</p>
	<p>
		<strong>Legal basis:</strong> your consent. You can withdraw it any time
		from the <a href="/cookies/#withdraw">cookie policy page</a>. If your browser
		sends a Global Privacy Control signal, we treat it as a decline and never
		load analytics.
	</p>
	<p>
		<strong>Where it goes:</strong> PostHog's EU ingest
		(<code>eu.i.posthog.com</code>) and EU-hosted storage.
	</p>

	<h3>Hosting and request logs</h3>
	<p>
		The site runs on Cloudflare. Cloudflare receives standard HTTP request
		metadata (IP, user agent, requested URL, timestamps) to serve and protect
		the site. The request logs are processed by Cloudflare on our behalf under
		their data-processing terms.
	</p>
	<p>
		<strong>Legal basis:</strong> legitimate interest in operating and
		protecting the website.
	</p>

	<h2>Who we share data with</h2>
	<p>
		We use the following sub-processors. We do not sell personal data, and we do
		not share it for advertising.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>PostHog Inc.</strong> — analytics, EU region.</li>
		<li><strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> — hosting and request handling.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>International transfers</h2>
	<p>
		Kurrent, Inc. is based in the United States. PostHog analytics data stays in
		the EU. Cloudflare operates a global network and may route requests through
		nodes outside your country.
	</p>

	<h2>Your rights</h2>
	<p>If your data is covered by GDPR or UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Ask what we hold about you (access)</li>
		<li>Correct anything wrong (rectification)</li>
		<li>Have it deleted (erasure)</li>
		<li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
		<li>Have it ported to another provider</li>
		<li>Withdraw consent for analytics at any time</li>
		<li>Complain to your local supervisory authority</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		To exercise any of these, email
		<a href="mailto:privacy@kurrent.io">privacy@kurrent.io</a>. We aim to respond
		within 30 days.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes</h2>
	<p>
		If we change this policy in a way that affects you, we will update the "last
		updated" date at the top and, where the change is material, give visible
		notice on the site.
	</p>
</StarlightPage>
